1
00:00:03,287 --> 00:00:06,134
When you come in connection 
with Kṛṣṇa consciousness substantial

2
00:00:06,134 --> 00:00:10,440
that the whole world of illusion,
that ‘māyām etāṁ taranti te’ [Bg: 7.14]—

3
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:13,144
you’ll crossover it 
as if it was

4
00:00:13,144 --> 00:00:18,744
the water left in the imprint
of the hoof of the calf.

5
00:00:19,094 --> 00:00:22,885
[Change of Perspective | 
To Relish Inconveniences]

6
00:00:22,885 --> 00:00:27,048
So what was oceanic—
kaler doṣa-nidhe rājann [SB: 12.3.51],

7
00:00:27,048 --> 00:00:33,738
what was oceanic in magnitude,
in proportion, the ocean of nescience,

8
00:00:34,322 --> 00:00:39,299
we are told, that ocean 
will be like a drop.

9
00:00:39,299 --> 00:00:43,056
What does it mean
but if change of perspective,

10
00:00:43,056 --> 00:00:46,138
sambandha-jñāna, 
reconceptualization—

11
00:00:46,138 --> 00:00:49,138
being reconfigured
to realize:

12
00:00:49,138 --> 00:00:58,128
I won’t find satisfaction,
fulfillment and identity as an exploiter,

13
00:00:58,128 --> 00:01:01,496
but rather as dedicating unit.

14
00:01:01,837 --> 00:01:05,681
When this transformation
takes place, that ocean,

15
00:01:05,681 --> 00:01:09,428
insurmountable ocean of nescience,
we are told, is reduced

16
00:01:09,428 --> 00:01:13,218
to the water left in the imprint
of the hoof of the calf.

17
00:01:15,377 --> 00:01:18,835
As if that wasn’t enough,
Viśvanāth Chakravartī Ṭhākur

18
00:01:18,835 --> 00:01:28,205
makes an interesting observation.
He says that … [Laughing]

19
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:35,615
He says, well … devotees 
in the devotional school …

20
00:01:35,615 --> 00:01:42,885
Govinda—we worship the cows.
So if it’s the water

21
00:01:42,898 --> 00:01:48,698
from the hoof print of the calf,
then it’s something good,

22
00:01:48,698 --> 00:01:54,234
it’s, like, sanctified. 
So, he says that

23
00:01:54,234 --> 00:01:57,234
another reading
of this verse—

24
00:01:57,234 --> 00:01:59,829
there are infinite levels
of interpretation—

25
00:01:59,829 --> 00:02:04,739
another way of reading it
is that all those things

26
00:02:04,739 --> 00:02:07,511
that are undesirable
in this world,

27
00:02:07,511 --> 00:02:13,114
they become for a devotee,
who is engaged in seva,

28
00:02:13,114 --> 00:02:16,114
pujala raga-patha gaurava bhange—

29
00:02:16,114 --> 00:02:19,500
something sacred to them.
What we told before,

30
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,750
Saraswatī T􏰅hākur said, 
“I relish doing these things.”

31
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:26,310
Bhakti Vinod 􏰅Thākur, “I relish whatever
inconvenience might come to me,

32
00:02:26,310 --> 00:02:27,588
if it’s in seva,

33
00:02:27,588 --> 00:02:31,938
then everything 
becomes transformed.”

34
00:02:31,938 --> 00:02:38,538
So, the so-called māyic existence
for the servitor,

35
00:02:38,538 --> 00:02:42,091
it turns in the something
completely different—

36
00:02:42,097 --> 00:02:47,851
everything is then seen
as an opportunity for dedication,

37
00:02:47,851 --> 00:02:50,821
for seva, 
for Kṛṣṇa consciousness.
 

38
00:02:50,821 --> 00:02:52,127
There’s a sloka, 
and it says,

39
00:02:52,127 --> 00:02:59,237
“Just as a businessman sees everything
as an opportunity for business,

40
00:02:59,237 --> 00:03:04,583
or someone who’s lusty
sees everything
 

41
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:09,083
as a potential fulfillment 
of their lust,

42
00:03:09,083 --> 00:03:14,303
for devotee then the whole world 
becomes inverted,

43
00:03:14,303 --> 00:03:22,123
and they see 
all serving potential.”

44
00:03:22,123 --> 00:03:26,312
So then it goes 
from mahā-māyā to yoga-māyā,

45
00:03:26,312 --> 00:03:31,682
yoga-māyā is also a kind of illusion:
mahā-māyā illusion, yoga-māyā illusion,

46
00:03:32,056 --> 00:03:36,083
but one taking us towards
the Absolute center,

47
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,363
and one taking us away.

